   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The following prerequisites must be met before configuring data sync:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">You must have credentials to the Dynamics environment where you will use the application to perform data sync. You must have the correct permissions to use the application.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Objects and fields to be synced must exist in both environments before running the data sync tool.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">The initial load is already complete between the two applications before running the data sync tool.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Any user account used to sync data must have the appropriate read, write, and delete permissions (in both Dynamics and Power).</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Field mapping must already exist for default fields like ExternalID and ModifiedOn for the objects to be synced.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Audits must be enabled in Dynamics for deleted records to be synced from Dynamics to Power.</li>
      </ul>
